problems.explanation:
At the top-right corner, all values below are larger and all values to the left are smaller. This makes each comparison eliminate one row or one column:

    std::pair<int,int> findSortedMatrix(const Matrix& a, double x) {
        int r = 0;
        int c = a.cols() - 1;
        while (r < a.rows() && c >= 0) {
            if (a(r, c) == x) return {r, c};
            if (a(r, c) > x) --c;
            else ++r;
        }
        return {-1, -1};
    }

The algorithm touches at most one cell per row plus one cell per column, so the complexity is $O(m+n)$ for an $m$ by $n$ matrix.

